# Map the @n3ary scope to GitHub Packages so consumers can
# `pnpm install @n3ary/gtfs-spec` and friends.
#
# Authentication: set NPM_TOKEN in your shell environment before
# running pnpm install. The auth line is NOT committed here on
# purpose — pnpm 11 refuses to expand env vars in project .npmrc
# (they could leak to an attacker-controlled registry).
#
# - In CI: set the NPM_TOKEN secret on this repo
#   (Settings → Secrets → Actions → NPM_TOKEN). The workflow
#   exports it as $NPM_TOKEN and uses pnpm config set to write
#   the credential to the user-level ~/.npmrc.
# - For local dev: export NPM_TOKEN in your shell, or add the
#   auth line to your user ~/.npmrc (not this project file).
#
# If the token isn't set, pnpm install will fail with E401. That's
# the intended signal — the package is private and requires auth.
@n3ary:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
